    "It is therefore possible that fact-checks in low-resource languages perform better than higher resource languages.",
    "The most salient point in the analysis of the multilingual misinformation is that the LLMs outperform the multilingual baseline when prompted with the English translation of the fact-checks.",
    "The variability in model performance across languages and the improvement of the accuracy when prompted with English language fact-checks indicates that the training regimen, in which the distribution of languages is highly skewed and English is dominant (Common Crawl Foundation, 2023), significantly impacts accuracy.",
